==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek [[ἀκρόπολις]], from [[ἄκρος]] ‘tip, peak’ + [[πόλις]] ‘city’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/əˈkrɒpəlɪs/}}

===Noun===
'''acropolis'''
# The raised fortified area of an ancient Greek city, especially with reference to that of Athens

